=== Noun ===

'''Kanji'''

# a way of representing [[Japanese]] words.  Kanji are borrowed from Chinese characters.  The word is derived from the Chinese word [[Hanzi]].  There are two main ways of reading them, the [[Kun]] (Japanese) reading and the [[On]] (Chinese) reading.  There is also a [[Nanori]] or name reading that is used for people and places.

